data.description: Advanced learning opportunities in Endocrinology and Reproductive Physiology (ERP) areas, particularly reproduction, with an emphasis on human health whenever possible. Explore scientific questions core to the ERP graduate training program at research level with further in-depth instruction and a focus on cutting-edge knowledge and developments. Topics include pregnancy (ovulation through parturition); embryonic growth and development; lactation biology; and neuroendocrinology. Continuation ofOBS&GYN 710. Intended for second- or third-year graduate students.
data.title: ADVANCED REPRODUCTIVE ENDOCRINE PHYSIOLOGY
